/-
  ActualMathematics/Physicality/RSDeltaClosure.lean

  Intrinsic Recognition-Science physicality for the δ arithmetic language.

  The physical carrier is not supplied by an empirical authority or by a
  caller-provided Peano model. It is the native multiplicative orbit

      1, 2, 2², 2³, ...

  inside the positive-ratio chart. Its zero is the identity ratio `1`; its
  successor is multiplication by the fixed base-two witness generator; and its
  comparison observable is the canonical reciprocal cost

      J(x / y) = ((x / y) + (x / y)⁻¹) / 2 - 1.

  The carrier is generated by the δ orbit, the successor is native
  multiplication, and J vanishes exactly when two physical states coincide.
  This is the non-relabeling content missing from an arbitrary `PeanoWorld`.

  CLAIM: CLOSED positive FOR intrinsic execution of empty-ledger generated
    δ theorems in the native J-recognition process.
  DOMAIN: `DFormula`, the generated natural stage, and the J-orbit on positive
    real ratios.
  PREMISES: the existing δ checker soundness theorem; the forced J-cost theorem;
    the native orbit construction with the selected base-two witness.
  REACH: every `GeneratedTheorem` is true under `msatJ` in the fixed J-orbit
    process, with its checker equation retained verbatim.
  does NOT license: a claim that a named laboratory instrument realizes this
    process, that J uniquely selects the generator `2`, exact empirical
    constants, or arbitrary mathematical structures outside the generated
    δ language.

  No project-local axioms. Every declaration is fully proved.
-/

